President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Richard C. Parker as Assistant Administrator of the United States Agency for International Development for Legislative and Public Affairs. Parker is currently the vice president of external affairs at Project Concern International and has previously served as director of communications at the United States Global Leadership Coalition and the Peace Corps. He has also held positions in communications, marketing, and policy in various sectors including the United States Department of Health and Human Services, Levi Strauss & Company, and the American Red Cross.

Additionally, President Trump intends to nominate Adrian Zuckerman as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to Romania. Zuckerman is a New York attorney and partner at the law firm Seyfarth Shaw LLP. He has previously held positions at Epstein Becker & Green, PC and Lowenstein Sandler, LLP. Zuckerman is also involved in philanthropic and educational initiatives, serving on the board of Kids Corp. and the alumni board of New York Law School. He immigrated to the United States from Romania at a young age and is fluent in Romanian.

President Trump also intends to appoint individuals to the Public Buildings Reform Board for six-year terms, but the names of the appointees are not mentioned in the article.